<TITLE> Relatives to sit in front of Rangs Bhaban until all bodies retrieved </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 14 (bdnews24.com)  Relatives of the three workers, whose bodies have been pulled from the rubble in Rangs Bhaban, have decided not to accept the bodies until those of all eight people, feared killed in the collapse, were found. The bodies of workers Ruhul Amin and Delwar Hossain, 45, and Jahid Mollah, 25, all from Faridpur district, recovered Thursday by the Fire Brigade rescue teams, were lying at the Dhaka Medical College Hospital morgue until Friday evening. The body of Aminul Islam, another worker killed when the 17thg floor of the building collapsed, was taken to his village home in Gaibandha by his relatives Friday afternoon. Relatives of the workers whose bodies were lying in the morgue as well as those who were waiting for the other missing persons announced that they would continue to sit in front of the Rangs Bhaban until they got the bodies of their loved ones. bdnews24.
